WEBVTT

00:00.468 --> 00:03.002
<i> PREVIOUSLY</i>
<i> ON "SECRETS AND LIES"...</i>

00:03.004 --> 00:04.169
I KNOW I'VE BEEN
ACTING CRAZY.
YEAH.

00:04.171 --> 00:05.504
BUT I STILL
CAN'T REMEMBER THAT NIGHT.

00:05.506 --> 00:07.272
I DIDN'T SAY SQUAT
TO CORNELL.

00:07.274 --> 00:10.109
SHE WANTED TO KNOW
IF YOU HAD A BLUE JACKET.

00:10.111 --> 00:11.611
<i> TYLER.</i>

00:11.612 --> 00:13.112
LISA,
IS TYLER BACK ALREADY?

00:13.114 --> 00:15.147
NO, NO,
MATTY'S CONFUSED.

00:15.149 --> 00:17.116
CAN'T JUST GO AROUND
HITTING PEOPLE, YOUNG LADY.

00:17.118 --> 00:19.351
HE CALLED YOU
A BABY KILLER.

00:19.353 --> 00:22.287
DID YOU CALL JESS MURPHY
THE NIGHT TOM WAS KILLED?
NO.

00:22.289 --> 00:24.456
BEN:
[<i> Slurring</i> ]<i> Jess, I don't know</i>
<i> what's gonna happen tomorrow.</i>

00:24.458 --> 00:26.658
<i> I just wanted to say...</i>
<i> I'm sorry.</i>

00:26.660 --> 00:29.428
CAN YOU EXPLAIN THAT,
MR. CRAWFORD?

00:30.231 --> 00:32.297
[ ELLIOTT MOSS' "SLIP" PLAYS ]

00:45.813 --> 00:51.183
¶ I WILL KEEP WATCHING YOU ¶

00:53.621 --> 00:59.258
¶ STRONGER NOW,
MAKE IT ALL RIGHT ¶

00:59.260 --> 01:01.060
¶ TO LET GO ¶

01:01.062 --> 01:02.494
[ VOCALIZING ]

01:06.067 --> 01:12.071
¶ ALL'S GONNA
SLIP, SLIP, SLIP THROUGH YA ¶

01:12.073 --> 01:16.742
¶ SLIP, SLIP, SLIP
THROUGH YOUR HANDS ¶

01:16.744 --> 01:18.610
[ GASPS ]
[ VOCALIZING ]

01:22.316 --> 01:26.452
¶ ALL'S GONNA
SLIP, SLIP, SLIP THROUGH YA ¶

01:26.454 --> 01:28.454
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
¶ SLIP, SLIP, SLIP
THROUGH YOUR HANDS ¶

01:28.456 --> 01:30.856
I CAN'T.
I CAN'T!

01:30.858 --> 01:32.124
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

01:38.699 --> 01:41.266
[ VOCALIZING ]

01:41.268 --> 01:43.602
[ DOOR CLOSES,
LOCK CLICKS ]
[ SIGHS ]

01:43.604 --> 01:45.304
[ WATER RUNNING ]

01:45.306 --> 01:46.572
[ SIGHS ]

01:54.548 --> 01:55.881
[ CELLPHONE BUZZING, RINGING ]

01:55.883 --> 01:56.849
Dave: I'M UP.

01:57.751 --> 01:59.318
[ MOANS ]

01:59.320 --> 02:00.586
[ MOANS ]

02:00.588 --> 02:01.386
[ BEEP ]

02:01.388 --> 02:03.122
[ SIGHS ]

02:03.123 --> 02:04.857
What is it?
What time is it?

02:04.859 --> 02:08.760
HEY, MAN, UH, THAT NIGHT
AT THE BAR, DID I CALL JESS?

02:08.762 --> 02:12.431
DUDE, IF I DON'T GET MY
14 HOURS, I'LL KILL SOMEBODY.

02:12.433 --> 02:13.765
Dave,
this is important.

02:13.767 --> 02:16.568
DID I CALL JESS
WHILE WE WERE STILL TOGETHER?

02:16.570 --> 02:17.803
I don't think so.

02:17.805 --> 02:19.605
I DON'T REMEMBER MUCH
FROM THAT NIGHT, BEN.

02:19.607 --> 02:21.457
I'M SORRY.

02:21.458 --> 02:23.308
YEAH, WELL,
I DON'T REMEMBER ANYTHING.

02:23.310 --> 02:25.544
So, now that we
got that settled,

02:25.546 --> 02:28.480
CAN YOU COME BY
AND FIX MY SINK FOR ME?

02:28.482 --> 02:30.916
YOU KNOW, YOU CAN LEARN
TO FIX THIS STUFF YOURSELF.

02:30.918 --> 02:34.186
WHY? I LEARNED HOW TO WORK
A PHONE AND CALL YOU.

02:34.188 --> 02:35.821
I CALLED YOU, DAVE.

02:35.823 --> 02:37.789
UM, LATER.

02:37.791 --> 02:39.825
[ BEEP ]

02:41.195 --> 02:42.728
[ WATER RUNNING ]

02:45.699 --> 02:47.166
[ WATER STOPS ]

02:47.168 --> 02:49.568
[ DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

02:49.570 --> 02:51.370
Abby: YAY, DAD!
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

02:51.372 --> 02:53.238
MOM SAID YOU WERE
GONNA SLEEP IN.

02:53.240 --> 02:54.873
GUESS MOM
WAS WRONG ABOUT ME.
[ BEEP ]

02:54.875 --> 02:56.075
CHRISTY CRAWFORD.

02:56.076 --> 02:57.276
I HAVE YOUR DAY
ALL PLANNED.

02:57.278 --> 02:58.810
FIRST, WE HAVE TO GO
TO THE STORE.

02:58.812 --> 03:00.579
I'M MAKING COOKIES
FOR NICKY'S PARTY.

03:00.581 --> 03:03.282
WHY CAN'T YOU EVER BE READY
FOR SCHOOL THIS EARLY?

03:03.284 --> 03:04.750
SCHOOL'S BORING.

03:04.752 --> 03:07.452
CHRISTMAS VACATION ISN'T.

03:07.454 --> 03:09.221
CAN WE GO WHEN
YOU'RE DONE WITH THAT?

03:09.223 --> 03:10.255
SURE.

03:11.358 --> 03:12.758
GOOD TIMES.

03:12.760 --> 03:14.860
Christy: [ LAUGHS ]
OF COURSE YOU WOULD.

03:14.862 --> 03:16.295
IT'S PERFECT.

03:16.297 --> 03:17.763
YEAH.

03:17.765 --> 03:18.764
YEAH.

03:18.766 --> 03:21.333
MM-HMM.

03:21.335 --> 03:22.601
NO, I CAN GET THERE.

03:23.737 --> 03:24.570
OKAY.

03:24.572 --> 03:26.572
OKAY, I'VE GOT TO GO.

03:26.574 --> 03:28.507
I'LL SEE YOU THERE.
YEAH.

03:28.509 --> 03:29.508
[ BEEP ]

03:29.510 --> 03:30.943
WHO WAS THAT?

03:30.945 --> 03:33.278
A CLIENT'S MAKING AN OFFER
ON A PROPERTY.

03:33.280 --> 03:34.746
OKAY.

03:34.748 --> 03:36.215
WHAT WAS THAT
THIS MORNING?

03:37.918 --> 03:39.685
SEX.

03:39.687 --> 03:41.853
THAT'S NOT
WHAT THAT WAS.

03:41.855 --> 03:43.722
I MIGHT BE LATE.

03:47.428 --> 03:48.794
[ DOOR OPENS ]

03:50.798 --> 03:52.397
WHAT?

03:52.399 --> 03:53.432
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

03:54.902 --> 03:56.835
YOU TELL ME.

03:58.606 --> 04:01.006
SHE JUST FORGOT
TO PUT THEM BACK ON.

04:02.876 --> 04:05.244
YOU GONNA COME SHOPPING
WITH ME AND ABBY?

04:05.246 --> 04:06.545
SORRY...

04:06.547 --> 04:09.848
GOT A SELF-IMMOLATION
I'D RATHER BE AT.

04:14.521 --> 04:16.421
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

04:18.892 --> 04:20.292
OH, HERE HE COMES.

04:21.795 --> 04:23.362
OH, LISTEN,
THEY'RE COMING.

04:24.365 --> 04:25.464
ALL RIGHT, BYE.

04:25.466 --> 04:28.634
Reporter:
WHERE ARE THE RICHARDSONS?
HAVE THEY MOVED?

04:28.636 --> 04:29.801
ARE YOU EXCITED
FOR TONIGHT?

04:29.803 --> 04:31.303
YEAH...

04:31.305 --> 04:33.805
ESPECIALLY SINCE I FOUND OUT
HANNAH'S NOT COMING.

04:33.807 --> 04:36.341
I THOUGHT YOU TWO
WERE BEST FRIENDS.

04:36.343 --> 04:38.043
THAT WAS
LAST YEAR, DAD.

04:38.045 --> 04:39.978
NOW SHE'S BEST FRIENDS
WITH KELLY.

04:39.980 --> 04:43.782
OH, THAT TYPE OF THING GOES ON
A LOT WITH GIRLS YOUR AGE.

04:43.784 --> 04:45.717
I DON'T CARE.

04:45.719 --> 04:47.686
IF HANNAH'S NOT COMING,
KELLY WON'T EITHER.

04:50.624 --> 04:53.525
DAD, MATT'S OUT ALONE.

04:58.832 --> 05:01.867
Ben: WHY DON'T YOU GO BACK TO
THE HOUSE WITH NATALIE?

05:01.869 --> 05:04.503
WAIT FOR ME THERE,
OKAY?
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

05:04.505 --> 05:05.737
MATTY!

05:10.544 --> 05:11.877
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

05:11.879 --> 05:14.346
MATTY, STOP!

05:18.852 --> 05:20.986
MATTY, STOP!

05:25.826 --> 05:26.892
STOP RUNNING!

05:53.821 --> 05:54.853
Matty:
[ WHIMPERS ]

05:56.423 --> 05:57.723
[ WHIMPERING ]

05:57.724 --> 05:59.024
MATTY, MATTY!
MATTY, JUST STAY THERE!

05:59.026 --> 06:00.492
[ SHOUTS ]
JUST STAY THERE.

06:00.494 --> 06:02.594
[ WHIMPERING ]

06:02.596 --> 06:03.995
YOU'RE OKAY.

06:07.134 --> 06:09.634
CALM DOWN, BUDDY.
COME ON.

06:09.636 --> 06:11.603
IT'S OKAY, MATTY.
IT'S OKAY!

06:11.605 --> 06:13.472
[ SHOUTING ]

06:15.142 --> 06:16.975
[ WHIMPERING ]

06:16.977 --> 06:18.777
LISTEN, MATTY,
YOU'RE OKAY!

06:18.779 --> 06:20.078
ALL RIGHT,
I WON'T TOUCH YOU!

06:20.080 --> 06:21.780
COME ON,
LET'S JUST GO HOME.

06:21.782 --> 06:22.714
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

06:22.716 --> 06:24.783
HOME, MATTY, OKAY?

06:24.785 --> 06:25.884
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

06:25.886 --> 06:27.953
COME ON. STAND UP.

06:32.059 --> 06:33.842
ALL RIGHT.

06:33.843 --> 06:35.626
WE'LL GET YOUR JACKET,
AND WE'LL GO HOME, OKAY?

06:36.797 --> 06:37.763
MATTY!

06:37.765 --> 06:38.897
Matty:
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

06:41.568 --> 06:43.068
[ SIGHS ]
DAMN IT.

06:43.070 --> 06:45.003
[ THUNDER RUMBLING ]

06:45.005 --> 06:47.606
MATTY, STOP RUNNING!

06:56.550 --> 06:57.549
COME ON!
COME ON.

06:57.551 --> 06:59.017
[ SHOUTS ]

06:59.018 --> 07:00.484
IT'S OKAY, BUD.
IT'S OKAY.

07:00.487 --> 07:01.553
[ WHIMPERING ]

07:03.924 --> 07:06.992
MATTY, MATTY, COME ON, MAN,
YOUR HOUSE IS RIGHT THERE!

07:06.994 --> 07:08.727
MATTY,
IT'S RIGHT THERE!

07:08.729 --> 07:09.995
COME ON.

07:09.997 --> 07:11.930
[ VEHICLE APPROACHES ]

07:17.471 --> 07:19.104
I FOUND MATT
IN THE WOODS!

07:19.106 --> 07:20.505
DID YOU
LEAVE HIM ALONE?!

07:20.507 --> 07:21.740
OH, MY GOD!

07:21.742 --> 07:23.475
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

07:23.477 --> 07:24.876
Ben: HE MADE IT ALL THE WAY
TO THE THE RIVER!

07:24.878 --> 07:26.978
THE RIVER?! HOLD THIS.
Ben: YEAH.

07:26.980 --> 07:28.113
MATTY.

07:28.115 --> 07:29.948
HONEY, COME ON,
WE'RE GONNA GO INSIDE

07:29.950 --> 07:31.917
AND PUT ON DRY CLOTHES
LIKE AFTER A BATH.

07:31.919 --> 07:34.019
OKAY, COME ON, BABY.
COME ON.

07:34.021 --> 07:35.554
KEEP HIM COVERED,
OKAY?
OKAY.

07:35.556 --> 07:36.855
COME ON, SWEETIE.

07:36.857 --> 07:37.956
IT'S OKAY.

07:37.958 --> 07:38.990
YOU'RE OKAY, BABY.

07:38.992 --> 07:41.059
IT'S OKAY.
IT'S OKAY.

07:41.061 --> 07:42.961
NO MORE RAIN, HONEY.

07:42.963 --> 07:44.463
IT'S OKAY, BABY.

07:44.464 --> 07:45.964
OKAY, ALMOST THERE,
ALMOST THERE.

07:45.966 --> 07:48.767
Matty:
[ WHIMPERING ]

07:48.769 --> 07:50.202
I KNOW, SWEETIE.
YEAH.

07:50.204 --> 07:51.670
GO ON,
LET'S GO GET DRY.

07:51.672 --> 07:53.538
Ben:
HEY, LISA!

07:53.540 --> 07:54.873
MATT WAS CARRYING
A BLUE JACKET.

07:54.875 --> 07:56.074
WAS THAT HIS?

07:57.544 --> 07:59.845
M-MATTY'S
A COLLECTOR.

07:59.847 --> 08:00.946
HE DOESN'T HAVE
A BLUE JACKET,

08:00.948 --> 08:02.581
BUT IF HE TOOK YOURS, BEN,
I'M SORRY.

08:07.955 --> 08:10.188
Ben:
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

08:30.978 --> 08:33.178
OKAY, ABBY.

08:34.147 --> 08:35.747
ABBY?

08:35.749 --> 08:37.115
Abby:
RIGHT HERE, DAD!

08:39.186 --> 08:40.969
READY TO GO?

08:40.970 --> 08:42.753
YEAH, BUT WE GOT TO STOP AT
THE POLICE STATION ON THE WAY.

08:42.756 --> 08:44.789
WHY? DO THEY KNOW
WHO KILLED TOM?

08:44.791 --> 08:48.627
NOT YET, BUT THERE'S SOMETHING
I HAVE TO TELL THE DETECTIVE.

08:50.731 --> 08:53.965
Woman:
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?!
THIS WILL ONLY TAKE
A FEW MINUTES.

08:53.967 --> 08:56.101
HAVE YOU NO SHAME?!
Cornell: I NEED YOU
TO LOWER YOUR VOICE.

08:56.103 --> 08:58.270
YOU ARE UNBELIEVABLE!

08:58.272 --> 08:59.971
Officer: MA'AM...
YOU KNOW WHAT YOU DID!

08:59.973 --> 09:02.674
STEP BACK, PLEASE.
YOU DESTROYED
MY HUSBAND!

09:02.676 --> 09:04.543
COME THIS WAY.
HOW DO YOU SLEEP?!

09:04.545 --> 09:06.878
JUST WAIT HERE
FOR ME, OKAY?

09:06.880 --> 09:08.280
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

09:13.887 --> 09:15.287
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

09:15.289 --> 09:17.289
I GIVE YOU
A KEY PIECE OF EVIDENCE,

09:17.291 --> 09:18.924
AND YOU'RE
NOT INTERESTED?

09:18.926 --> 09:20.725
A BLUE JACKET
WITH A BLOOD STAIN --

09:20.727 --> 09:21.993
I'M VERY INTERESTED.

09:21.995 --> 09:24.095
NOW, I DON'T KNOW
HOW MATT GOT IT,

09:24.096 --> 09:26.196
BUT I'D ASSUME THAT
THE JACKET WOULD HAVE
TOM'S KILLER'S DNA ON IT.

09:26.199 --> 09:28.833
WAS THIS YOUR JACKET?
WHAT?!

09:28.835 --> 09:31.970
HOW DO YOU KNOW TOM'S KILLER
HAD A BLUE JACKET?

09:31.972 --> 09:34.072
FROM YOU!

09:34.073 --> 09:36.173
YOU ASKED DAVE
IF I HAD A BLUE JA--

09:36.176 --> 09:40.245
I SAW A BLUE JACKET IN THE WOODS
WITH A BLOODSTAIN ON IT.

09:40.247 --> 09:41.746
I THOUGHT YOU'D
WANT TO KNOW!

09:41.748 --> 09:43.281
AND IT'S MISSING.

09:44.117 --> 09:45.850
YEAH, IT WASN'T THERE
WHEN I WENT BACK.

09:45.852 --> 09:47.752
YOU DO SEE MY DILEMMA --

09:47.754 --> 09:50.121
YOU HEARD I NEEDED EVIDENCE,
YOU GAVE ME EVIDENCE,

09:50.123 --> 09:53.158
AND NOW THE ALLEGED EVIDENCE
IS CONVENIENTLY MISSING,

09:53.160 --> 09:54.993
LIKE YOUR FLASHLIGHT.

09:54.995 --> 09:56.928
[ SIGHS ]
I'LL FIND IT MYSELF.

09:56.930 --> 09:58.697
YOU DON'T NEED
TO DO ANYTHING,

09:58.699 --> 10:01.967
EXCEPT MAYBE FIND SOMEBODY
WHO CAN CORROBORATE YOUR STORY.

10:01.969 --> 10:03.902
IS THAT A POSSIBILITY,
MR. CRAWFORD?

10:15.882 --> 10:17.082
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

10:17.084 --> 10:19.351
TAKE THESE IN, HON.

10:24.758 --> 10:27.392
YOU JUST WON'T BE HAPPY UNTIL
THE WHOLE NEIGHBORHOOD IS GONE.

10:27.394 --> 10:28.860
HELLO, KEVIN.

10:28.862 --> 10:31.296
NOT ENOUGH YOU GOT
SCOTT MURPHY TURNED IN

10:31.298 --> 10:32.964
AND FORCED
THE RICHARDSONS TO LEAVE.

10:32.966 --> 10:34.132
NOW YOU'RE PESTERING
LISA?

10:34.134 --> 10:36.101
I'M NOT PESTERING
ANYONE.

10:36.103 --> 10:38.336
MATT ALMOST DROWNED.
I TOOK HIM HOME.

10:38.338 --> 10:40.405
ALWAYS AN EXCUSE.

10:42.809 --> 10:44.409
BEST TAKE STOCK, SON.

10:45.846 --> 10:47.012
THANKS, KEVIN.

10:47.014 --> 10:48.046
APPRECIATE THE CONCERN.

10:48.048 --> 10:50.015
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

11:06.233 --> 11:07.932
Tyler: DAMN.

11:07.934 --> 11:09.868
NO PLACE IS SAFE.

11:09.870 --> 11:11.036
TYLER?

11:15.809 --> 11:17.275
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?

11:17.277 --> 11:21.012
OH, IT'S JUST A HAND ROLL,
MR. CRAWFORD.

11:21.014 --> 11:22.147
TOBACCO.

11:22.149 --> 11:23.181
[ CHUCKLES ]
IT'S NO BIG DEAL.

11:23.183 --> 11:25.316
UH, NO, UM...

11:25.318 --> 11:27.385
YOUR MOM SAID YOU WERE STAYING
AT SCHOOL FOR CHRISTMAS.

11:27.387 --> 11:29.888
OH. CHANGE OF PLANS.

11:30.991 --> 11:33.191
SOMETHING HAPPEN?
SHE OKAY?

11:33.193 --> 11:34.759
YEAH, MOM'S GREAT.

11:34.761 --> 11:38.229
IT'S A HOLIDAY.
FAMILIES SHOULD BE TOGETHER.

11:48.041 --> 11:50.775
HEY, DON'T WORRY.
NAT DOESN'T HANG OUT HERE.

11:50.777 --> 11:52.077
I SAW HER ONCE,
SENT HER HOME.

11:52.079 --> 11:53.812
SHE'S A GOOD KID.

11:55.382 --> 11:57.182
WELL, SHE'LL
WANT TO SEE YOU,

11:57.184 --> 11:59.250
SO I'LL JUST SEND HER BY
TO SAY HELLO.

11:59.252 --> 12:01.186
OH, IT'S PROBABLY BETTER
IF I CALL HER.

12:01.188 --> 12:03.488
MY MOM HAS
STUFF PLANNED, SO...

12:05.158 --> 12:08.159
WELL,
I SHOULD GET BACK.

12:08.161 --> 12:09.728
PROBABLY LATE
FOR SOMETHING ALREADY.

12:10.897 --> 12:12.263
DID YOU SEE
A BLUE JACKET OUT HERE?

12:13.800 --> 12:15.266
NO.

12:15.268 --> 12:16.868
UM...

12:16.870 --> 12:18.970
YOU MIND NOT TELLING MY MOM
THAT YOU SAW ME?

12:18.972 --> 12:20.805
SHE HATES WHEN I SMOKE.
SURE.

12:20.807 --> 12:21.973
COOL.

12:26.379 --> 12:28.313
SO, UH...

12:28.315 --> 12:30.515
DID TELLING DEPUTY DO-RIGHT
ABOUT THE JACKET

12:30.517 --> 12:31.883
GET HER
OFF YOUR BACK?

12:31.885 --> 12:33.251
NO.
[ SIGHS ]

12:33.253 --> 12:34.819
SHE'S LOOKING AT ME

12:34.821 --> 12:37.455
LIKE I'M MORE GUILTY
AND MAKING UP EVIDENCE.

12:37.457 --> 12:39.207
WELL, YOU BETTER
FIND IT, MAN,

12:39.208 --> 12:40.958
'CAUSE I'M NOT GOING OUT
ON ANOTHER MEAL WITH THAT CHICK.

12:40.961 --> 12:42.639
SHE'S SCARY.

12:42.640 --> 12:44.318
I WENT BACK
TO LOOK FOR IT,

12:44.319 --> 12:45.997
AND THAT'S WHEN I SAW TYLER DALY
IN THE WOODS OUT FOR A SMOKE.

12:45.999 --> 12:47.332
WEED?

12:47.334 --> 12:49.033
NO, HE SAID
IT WAS A CIGARETTE.

12:49.870 --> 12:51.069
YEAH, ALL RIGHT.

12:51.071 --> 12:52.971
WELL, IT FIGURES.
[ GRUNTS ]

12:52.973 --> 12:54.539
HE'S MORE OF
A PHARM BOY, ACTUALLY.

12:56.243 --> 12:57.475
PHARMACEUTICALS.

12:57.477 --> 12:58.843
[ BLOWS ]

12:58.845 --> 13:00.078
HE'S BEEN
IN AND OUT OF REHAB.

13:01.448 --> 13:02.781
HOW DO YOU KNOW?

13:03.550 --> 13:06.050
UM...NATALIE TOLD ME.

13:06.052 --> 13:08.219
OH, MAN, THAT WAS
SUPPOSED TO BE A SECRET.

13:08.221 --> 13:09.954
DAMN!

13:09.956 --> 13:12.957
WHY DO I SUCK SO MUCH
AT SECRETS?

13:12.959 --> 13:14.993
PEOPLE SHOULDN'T
TELL ME STUFF.

13:14.995 --> 13:17.028
EXCEPT FOR YOU.

13:17.030 --> 13:19.798
UH, YOU KNOW I'M GONNA
TAKE YOUR SECRETS TO
THE GRAVE WITH ME, RIGHT?

13:21.501 --> 13:24.936
TYLER BEING AN ADDICT
EXPLAINS A LOT.

13:24.938 --> 13:26.838
HE'S USING AGAIN.

13:26.840 --> 13:28.406
HE HAD SCRATCHES
ON HIS KNUCKLES,

13:28.408 --> 13:30.041
AND LISA
HAD A SPLIT LIP.

13:30.043 --> 13:32.343
MAYBE HE'S VIOLENT
AND SHE'S SCARED.

13:32.345 --> 13:34.312
WAIT, WAIT, WAIT.
WHAT?

13:34.314 --> 13:37.115
MAYBE YOU'RE ON THE FAST BUS
TO CRAZY TOWN, MAN.

13:37.117 --> 13:38.516
TYLER IS A GOOD KID.

13:38.518 --> 13:41.586
HE'S GOT, LIKE,
A TINY CRIMINAL RECORD.

13:41.588 --> 13:44.322
IF HE WAS ON SOMETHING
AND KILLED TOM,

13:44.324 --> 13:46.424
THAT WOULD EXPLAIN
WHY MATT HAD THE JACKET

13:46.426 --> 13:47.959
AND WHY IT DISAPPEARED.

13:49.296 --> 13:50.995
O-KAY.

13:50.997 --> 13:53.097
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?
[ SIGHS ]

13:53.099 --> 13:55.099
YOU NEED A NEW TRAP COUPLING.
I DON'T HAVE ONE IN MY KIT.

13:55.101 --> 13:57.902
I CAN COME BACK,
JUST NOT TODAY.

13:57.904 --> 14:00.305
YOU NEED WATER
ANYTIME SOON?

14:00.307 --> 14:02.473
[ SNIFFS ]

14:02.475 --> 14:03.875
NAH, I'M FINE.

14:03.877 --> 14:05.109
THAT'S FOUL.

14:11.184 --> 14:12.283
[ ENGINE SHUTS OFF ]

14:12.285 --> 14:13.668
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

14:13.669 --> 14:15.052
Reporter: HERE HE COMES.
ROLL CAMERA. ROLL, ROLL.

14:15.055 --> 14:17.155
MR. CRAWFORD...
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

14:17.157 --> 14:19.257
[ CAMERA SHUTTERS CLICKING ]

14:19.259 --> 14:21.292
YOU MIND JUST
A QUICK QUESTION?

14:21.294 --> 14:22.527
JUST FOR A SECOND.

14:22.529 --> 14:24.429
Reporter #2:
REPORTING FOR CHANNEL 37.

14:24.431 --> 14:26.030
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

14:26.032 --> 14:27.031
ONE STATEMENT,
PLEASE!

14:27.033 --> 14:28.550
DID DETECTIVE CORNELL...

14:28.551 --> 14:30.068
Jess:
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

14:30.070 --> 14:32.604
[ CRYING ]

14:36.610 --> 14:38.076
[ SNIFFLES ]

14:38.078 --> 14:39.644
I'M S--

14:39.646 --> 14:42.614
I FORGOT.

14:42.616 --> 14:44.382
IT WAS FOR CHRISTMAS.

14:44.384 --> 14:46.017
[ BREATHING SHAKILY ]

14:47.120 --> 14:49.988
GO INSIDE. I'LL TAKE CARE
OF SENDING IT BACK.

14:49.990 --> 14:52.323
MR. CRAWFORD?

14:54.094 --> 14:55.260
MR. CRAWFORD?

14:55.262 --> 14:56.995
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

14:58.365 --> 15:00.064
Christy: MM, WOW!

15:00.066 --> 15:01.633
OH, THOSE LOOK GREAT,
SWEETHEART.

15:01.635 --> 15:03.434
THANKS, MOM.

15:03.436 --> 15:05.169
READY TO GO, MONKEY?

15:05.171 --> 15:07.105
ALMOST --
JUST NEED MY SHOES.

15:14.214 --> 15:15.079
ABOUT THIS MORNING --

15:15.081 --> 15:16.614
OH, IT WENT
REALLY WELL.

15:16.616 --> 15:18.516
WE'RE JUST WAITING
ON A COUNTER OFFER.

15:18.518 --> 15:20.585
YOU AND THE GUY
WHO BOUGHT YOU THE EARRINGS

15:20.587 --> 15:22.120
AND TOOK YOU
TO DINNER?

15:23.056 --> 15:24.222
SAM'S JUST A CLIENT.

15:25.091 --> 15:26.457
DOES HE KNOW THAT?

15:26.459 --> 15:29.093
CHRISTY, I KNOW YOU'RE
PROBABLY LOOKING AT THIS GUY,

15:29.095 --> 15:32.530
THINKING HOW MUCH EASIER
IT WOULD BE.

15:32.532 --> 15:33.932
WE BOTH MADE MISTAKES,

15:33.934 --> 15:36.034
BUT THAT DOESN'T ERASE
17 YEARS OF MARRIAGE.

15:36.036 --> 15:37.669
IT DOESN'T ERASE
OUR FAMILY.

15:37.671 --> 15:40.104
SAM IS JUST A CLIENT.

15:43.576 --> 15:46.044
READY, DADDY!

15:47.714 --> 15:49.981
HAVE FUN.

15:49.983 --> 15:51.249
OKAY.

15:55.555 --> 15:57.255
[ DOORBELL RINGS ]

16:02.562 --> 16:04.295
Roger: HEY.

16:04.297 --> 16:07.632
HEY, I GUESS YOUR PARENTS DIDN'T
TELL YOU IT WAS CANCELED.

16:07.634 --> 16:10.068
HE'S RIGHT
OVER THERE.

16:10.070 --> 16:12.971
LET'S, UH, LET'S
GO TALK TO HIM REAL QUICK.

16:21.414 --> 16:23.748
BEN, I'M SORRY
ABOUT THE MIX-UP.

16:23.750 --> 16:25.717
PARTY'S NOT TONIGHT?

16:25.719 --> 16:27.085
UH...

16:27.087 --> 16:28.286
ACTUALLY,
IT WAS CANCELED.

16:28.287 --> 16:29.486
WE PROBABLY SHOULD'VE
CALLED EVERYONE

16:29.489 --> 16:32.023
INSTEAD OF SENDING OUT
AN E-MAIL.

16:36.029 --> 16:37.996
ABBY, GO WAIT
BY THE TRUCK.

16:40.300 --> 16:42.734
WHAT THE HELL, MAN?
THERE'S KIDS IN THERE.

16:42.736 --> 16:44.469
I KNOW.
I'M SORRY.

16:44.471 --> 16:46.270
BUT UNDER THE CIRCUMSTANCES,
WE JUST COULDN'T --

16:46.272 --> 16:48.106
I KNOW WHAT THEY'RE
SAYING ABOUT ME,

16:48.108 --> 16:49.273
BUT DON'T
PUNISH ABBY FOR IT.

16:49.275 --> 16:51.075
BEN, I'M TRYING TO BE
THE GOOD GUY HERE.

16:51.077 --> 16:52.477
THEN BE THE GOOD GUY.

16:52.479 --> 16:53.778
I'LL HAVE CHRISTY OR NATALIE
PICK HER UP.

16:53.780 --> 16:55.013
I WON'T SHOW MY FACE.

16:55.015 --> 16:56.548
IT WON'T HELP.

16:56.549 --> 16:58.082
AFTER WHAT HAPPENED
AT THE WINTER FAIR,

16:58.084 --> 17:00.018
ABBY JUST
CAN'T BE HERE.

17:00.020 --> 17:02.720
IT'S NOT JUST US, BEN.
ALL RIGHT?

17:02.722 --> 17:04.155
ALL THE OTHER PARENTS
AGREED.

17:04.157 --> 17:05.790
I'M SORRY.

17:08.428 --> 17:10.028
[ DOOR OPENS ]

17:10.030 --> 17:11.062
[ KEYS JINGLE ]

17:11.064 --> 17:12.563
[ SIGHS ]

17:12.565 --> 17:14.132
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

17:15.502 --> 17:18.102
I'M SORRY, HONEY.

17:18.104 --> 17:19.470
LET'S GO HOME.

17:24.177 --> 17:26.210
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

17:33.820 --> 17:35.586
Ben: COULD NICKY SHOW YOU
A GOOD TIME LIKE THIS?

17:35.588 --> 17:37.455
NO.
YOU'RE MUCH MORE FUN.

17:37.456 --> 17:39.323
PLUS, YOU'RE NOT FRIENDS
WITH HANNAH AND KELLY.

17:39.325 --> 17:40.825
I USED TO BE,

17:40.827 --> 17:43.061
BUT THEY DON'T INVITE ME
FOR SLEEPOVERS ANYMORE.

17:43.063 --> 17:44.529
I DON'T KNOW WHY.

17:44.531 --> 17:45.596
[ LAUGHS ]

17:48.568 --> 17:50.101
I'M GLAD YOU'RE
DOING OKAY, HONEY,

17:50.103 --> 17:51.569
BUT LET'S NOT FORGET
WHY WE'RE HERE TONIGHT.

17:51.571 --> 17:54.238
THOSE PARENTS MADE A CHOICE
I DIDN'T LIKE,

17:54.240 --> 17:56.140
BUT THEY HAD A REASON.

17:56.776 --> 17:58.743
THE WINTER FAIR.
YEAH.

17:58.745 --> 18:01.145
ACTIONS HAVE CONSEQUENCES,
ABBY.

18:02.348 --> 18:03.748
BUT THAT KID
CALLED YOU --
I KNOW.

18:03.750 --> 18:05.516
I KNOW.

18:05.518 --> 18:07.785
JUST BECAUSE HE'S A JERK DOESN'T
MEAN IT'S OKAY TO HIT HIM.

18:07.787 --> 18:09.787
THAT'S NEVER
THE ANSWER.

18:11.357 --> 18:14.358
AS CONSEQUENCES
FOR MY COOKIES BEING GONE,

18:14.360 --> 18:17.195
CAN WE HAVE
ICE CREAM, TOO?

18:17.197 --> 18:18.830
[ CHUCKLES SOFTLY ]

18:18.832 --> 18:20.164
FINISH YOUR BURGER.

18:20.166 --> 18:22.266
THEN WE'LL TALK.

18:22.268 --> 18:23.501
[ SLURPS ]

18:28.441 --> 18:30.141
Christy: BEN!

18:35.148 --> 18:36.447
[ SIGHS ]

18:39.419 --> 18:40.518
YOU NEED TO REPORT IT.

18:40.520 --> 18:41.786
TO WHO?

18:41.788 --> 18:43.855
CORNELL?

18:43.857 --> 18:46.757
SHE'S NOT
GONNA DO ANYTHING.

18:46.759 --> 18:48.826
I USE THIS CAR
FOR BUSINESS.

18:48.828 --> 18:50.461
YOU CAN TAKE
MY TRUCK.

18:54.534 --> 18:57.168
I HAVE A HOUSE INSPECTION
IN AN HOUR.

18:57.170 --> 19:00.338
IF YOU'RE NOT GONNA CALL HER,
I WILL.

19:02.308 --> 19:03.674
[ SIGHS ]

19:03.676 --> 19:06.544
[ DOOR OPENS AND CLOSES ]

19:17.257 --> 19:18.656
[ SIGHS ]

19:18.658 --> 19:20.224
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]

19:24.731 --> 19:26.164
CAN I TALK TO TYLER?

19:26.166 --> 19:28.366
WELL [SIGHS]
I ALREADY TOLD YOU,

19:28.368 --> 19:30.268
TYLER IS STAYING AT SCHOOL
FOR THE HOLIDAYS.

19:30.270 --> 19:31.836
LISA, I SAW HIM
IN THE WOODS.

19:31.838 --> 19:34.472
WELL, I DON'T SEE
HOW THAT'S POSSIBLE.

19:34.474 --> 19:35.806
HE TRASHED
CHRISTY'S CAR,

19:35.808 --> 19:37.842
HE LET MATT OUT ALONE,
AND WHAT HE DID TO YOU...

19:37.844 --> 19:38.910
[ SCOFFS ]

19:40.413 --> 19:42.346
IF YOU'RE HAVING TROUBLE
WITH TYLER,

19:42.348 --> 19:44.649
LYING ABOUT IT'S
NOT GONNA HELP.

19:46.653 --> 19:48.753
KEVIN WARNED ME
ABOUT YOU.

19:49.756 --> 19:51.923
AND I TOLD HIM
THAT HE WAS WRONG,

19:51.925 --> 19:53.858
BUT NOW
YOU KEEP HARASSING ME.

19:54.894 --> 19:56.661
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

19:56.663 --> 19:57.562
I GOT TO GO.

19:58.731 --> 19:59.797
WILL YOU JUST --

19:59.799 --> 20:01.866
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

20:06.439 --> 20:09.640
I REALLY SHOULD
GET GOING.
I KNOW.

20:09.642 --> 20:11.576
Christy: DO YOU HAVE
ALL THE PHOTOGRAPHS YOU NEED?

20:11.578 --> 20:13.744
YOU'RE FREE TO TAKE THE CAR,
MRS. CRAWFORD.

20:13.746 --> 20:16.214
I'LL JUST FINISH UP HERE
WITH YOUR HUSBAND.

20:16.215 --> 20:18.683
UH, HONEY, UNLESS, DO YOU WANT
ME TO FOLLOW YOU TO THE SHOP?

20:18.685 --> 20:21.586
NO, MY CLIENT'S
PICKING ME UP.

20:25.425 --> 20:26.924
[ CAR DOOR CLOSES ]

20:26.926 --> 20:28.626
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

20:28.628 --> 20:30.394
ANY LUCK...

20:30.396 --> 20:31.896
FINDING YOUR JACKET?

20:31.898 --> 20:34.365
IT'S NOT MINE,
AND NO.

20:35.401 --> 20:36.867
ARE YOU GONNA
TALK TO TYLER DALY?

20:37.704 --> 20:40.438
THIS IS CANNABIS,
NOT TOBACCO.

20:40.440 --> 20:41.973
THE KID WENT TO REHAB.

20:41.975 --> 20:44.942
YOU SHOULDN'T JUMP
TO CONCLUSIONS, MR. CRAWFORD.

20:44.944 --> 20:47.245
HIS MOTHER IS LYING
ABOUT WHERE HE IS.

20:47.247 --> 20:49.447
HE HAD SCRATCHES
ON HIS KNUCKLES.

20:49.449 --> 20:50.948
THERE'S SOMETHING
GOING ON IN THAT HOUSE,

20:50.950 --> 20:52.850
AND I'M TELLING YOU,
IT'S CONNECTED TO TOM'S MURDER.

20:52.852 --> 20:54.619
YOU ALSO THOUGHT

20:54.620 --> 20:56.387
THE RICHARDSONS HAD SOMETHING
TO DO WITH TOM'S MURDER.

20:58.324 --> 21:00.958
TYLER VANDALIZED THE FENCE
AND CHRISTY'S CAR.

21:00.960 --> 21:03.961
[ PEN CLICKS ]
HE'S TRYING TO DIVERT ATTENTION
FROM HIM TO ME.

21:04.931 --> 21:06.264
OH, YOU'RE
TAKING IT SERIOUSLY?

21:06.899 --> 21:09.767
I TAKE EVERYTHING
SERIOUSLY.

21:09.769 --> 21:12.336
YOUR SITUATION REMINDS ME
OF THE HALCRO CASE.

21:12.939 --> 21:15.973
MR. HALCRO WAS MURDERED, AND
SHORTLY INTO THE INVESTIGATION,

21:15.975 --> 21:17.842
HIS WIFE CALLED ME UP

21:17.844 --> 21:21.579
AND SAID SHE HAD RECEIVED
A THREATENING GREETING CARD

21:21.581 --> 21:24.315
AND FEARED FOR HER LIFE.

21:24.316 --> 21:27.050
AND, EVENTUALLY, I REALIZED THAT
SHE HAD SENT THE CARD HERSELF.

21:27.053 --> 21:32.356
SHE WANTED TO BE VIEWED MORE
AS A VICTIM, NOT AS A SUSPECT.

21:32.358 --> 21:34.842
BUT IN THE END,

21:34.843 --> 21:37.327
SHE WAS CONVICTED OF FALSIFYING
A POLICE REPORT AND...

21:37.330 --> 21:38.329
[ PEN CLICKS ]

21:38.331 --> 21:39.830
...MURDER.

21:39.832 --> 21:43.401
I DID NOT VANDALIZE
MY OWN PROPERTY.

21:43.403 --> 21:45.987
MAYBE NOT,

21:45.988 --> 21:48.572
BUT YOUR FENCE WAS DEFACED
WITH PAINT THAT WASHES OFF --

21:48.574 --> 21:49.740
ONE LIKE THIS.

21:50.610 --> 21:51.876
AND YOUR WIFE'S CAR

21:51.878 --> 21:55.479
WAS VANDALIZED
WITH PAINT CLEANER LIKE THIS.

21:58.084 --> 22:01.686
BUT I MAYBE I SHOULDN'T
JUMP TO CONCLUSIONS, EITHER.

22:04.857 --> 22:06.457
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]

22:16.069 --> 22:18.836
HEY, NAT...
[ SIGHS ]

22:18.838 --> 22:20.871
IS TYLER DALY VIOLENT?

22:20.873 --> 22:22.673
WHAT?

22:22.675 --> 22:24.075
I KNOW HE'S AN ADDICT.

22:24.077 --> 22:25.976
WHEN HE'S ON SOMETHING,
IS HE VIOLENT?

22:27.046 --> 22:29.413
I'M NEVER TELLING DAVE
ANYTHING AGAIN,

22:29.415 --> 22:30.881
AND I'M NOT
SNITCHING ON TYLER.

22:30.883 --> 22:33.117
HONEY, I DON'T CARE ABOUT
THE DRUGS OR WHATEVER HE'S INTO.

22:33.119 --> 22:34.785
I'M BEING
ACCUSED OF MURDER.

22:34.787 --> 22:37.421
I NEED INFORMATION.

22:37.423 --> 22:39.056
THERE'S NO WAY
HE DID ANYTHING TO TOM.

22:40.793 --> 22:42.793
I DON'T KNOW.

22:42.795 --> 22:44.895
SOMETHING'S NOT RIGHT
IN THE DALY HOUSE.

22:44.897 --> 22:46.931
I JUST NEED TO KNOW
WHAT YOU KNOW.

22:46.933 --> 22:49.533
I ONLY SAW HIM
LOSE IT ONCE,

22:49.535 --> 22:52.136
RIGHT BEFORE HE WENT
INTO REHAB THE FIRST TIME.

22:52.138 --> 22:54.071
TYLER'S A NICE GUY, DAD.

22:54.073 --> 22:55.406
YOU SHOULD SEE HIM
WITH MATT.

22:55.408 --> 22:56.640
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

22:56.642 --> 22:57.875
Christy:
[ SIGHS ]

22:57.877 --> 22:59.143
Natalie: OH, GOOD,
YOU GUYS ARE GOING OUT.

22:59.145 --> 23:00.711
Christy: OH, I AM --

23:00.713 --> 23:02.480
CELEBRATING WITH A CLIENT.
WE CLOSED ON THE HOUSE.

23:02.482 --> 23:03.781
CAN'T YOU TAKE HIM?

23:03.783 --> 23:05.583
TONE.

23:05.585 --> 23:06.851
DO YOU NEED A RIDE OR...

23:06.853 --> 23:08.453
OH, I CALLED
A CAB ALREADY,

23:08.454 --> 23:10.054
UH, BUT TOMORROW, COULD YOU
PICK ME UP AFTER MY SHOWING?

23:10.056 --> 23:11.889
MY CAR
WILL BE READY THEN.

23:11.891 --> 23:12.790
SURE.

23:12.792 --> 23:14.725
HEY, GOOD NIGHT!

23:14.727 --> 23:16.627
[ DOOR OPENS ]

23:16.629 --> 23:18.129
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

23:18.131 --> 23:20.498
ARE YOU GUYS
GETTING A DIVORCE?

23:21.667 --> 23:23.734
[ TAPS ON COUNTER ]

23:23.736 --> 23:25.703
NATALIE, I LOVE YOU,

23:25.705 --> 23:27.571
BUT WHAT'S GOING ON
IN OUR MARRIAGE

23:27.573 --> 23:28.873
IS NONE OF YOUR BUSINESS.

23:28.875 --> 23:31.075
BUT MY ENTIRE LIFE
IS YOUR BUSINESS?

23:32.578 --> 23:33.811
PRETTY MUCH. YEAH.

23:33.813 --> 23:35.946
HEY!

23:46.526 --> 23:47.792
[ SIGHS ]

24:23.029 --> 24:24.829
[ BEEP ]

24:24.831 --> 24:26.564
[ GARAGE DOOR WHIRS ]

24:46.219 --> 24:49.487
WHAT'S ALL THIS,
MR. CRAWFORD?

24:49.489 --> 24:50.888
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

24:50.890 --> 24:53.057
YOU TEXTED ME.
YOU ASKED ME TO COME.

24:53.059 --> 24:54.592
NO, I DIDN'T.

24:59.966 --> 25:01.966
MR. CRAWFORD, I NEED YOU
TO STEP AWAY.

25:01.968 --> 25:03.200
THIS IS A CRIME SCENE.

25:09.575 --> 25:11.809
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

25:11.811 --> 25:13.177
I'M REALLY SORRY
I HAVE TO GO.

25:13.179 --> 25:14.879
IT'S FINE.

25:14.881 --> 25:16.714
GIRLS ARE OKAY,
I'M OKAY.

25:16.716 --> 25:18.549
YEAH, BUT THESE THINGS,
THEY KEEP HAPPENING.

25:18.551 --> 25:19.650
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

25:19.652 --> 25:21.118
IT'S JUST A PRANK.

25:21.120 --> 25:22.887
I SHOULD BE DONE
AROUND 2:00.

25:22.889 --> 25:25.856
THE ADDRESS
IS ON THE FRIDGE.

25:25.858 --> 25:27.725
GOT IT.

25:27.727 --> 25:28.726
GOOD LUCK.

25:28.728 --> 25:30.895
THANK YOU.

25:32.131 --> 25:33.931
Reporter: BEN, PLEASE!
Reporter #2: MR. CRAWFORD!

25:33.933 --> 25:35.866
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

25:35.868 --> 25:37.968
Reporter #3: WHY ARE DETECTIVES
IN YOUR GARAGE, SIR?

25:37.970 --> 25:39.570
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

25:39.572 --> 25:41.539
NONE OF YOUR NEIGHBORS
SAW ANYTHING,

25:41.541 --> 25:44.275
AND MY TECHS
DIDN'T FIND ANY PRINTS.

25:44.277 --> 25:47.578
WHOEVER DID THIS KNOWS THE PRESS
IS HERE FROM 9:00 TO 9:00.

25:47.580 --> 25:48.879
WHAT'S MORE TROUBLING IS,

25:48.881 --> 25:51.315
THEY KNOW HOW TO GET
CLASSIFIED INFORMATION.

25:51.317 --> 25:53.617
THE FLASHLIGHT
HAD NOT BEEN MADE PUBLIC.

25:54.186 --> 25:55.953
MAYBE YOUR OFFICE
HAD ANOTHER LEAK.

25:57.757 --> 25:59.189
IT'S PROBABLY
THE SAME MORON

25:59.191 --> 26:01.525
WHO TRASHED MY FENCE
AND CHRISTY'S CAR.

26:01.527 --> 26:03.894
THOSE WERE JUVENILE
ACTS OF VANDALISM.

26:03.896 --> 26:06.263
THIS TOOK PLANNING
AND SOPHISTICATION.

26:06.265 --> 26:07.998
IT'S AN EXPLICIT THREAT.

26:08.000 --> 26:09.833
IT'S FLASHLIGHTS.

26:09.835 --> 26:12.002
IT'S THE MURDER WEAPON --

26:12.004 --> 26:14.004
LOTS OF THEM.

26:14.006 --> 26:17.675
MR. CRAWFORD, I NEED TO BE SURE
THAT YOU KNOW THIS IS SERIOUS.

26:17.677 --> 26:19.577
I'LL COMPILE
A THREAT ASSESSMENT,

26:19.579 --> 26:21.579
BUT IN THE MEANTIME...

26:21.581 --> 26:23.180
YOU NEED
TO WATCH YOUR BACK.

26:24.650 --> 26:26.116
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

26:27.587 --> 26:29.820
DO YOU THINK
UNCLE MICHAEL

26:29.822 --> 26:31.855
WILL MAKE US EAT
THAT STUPID FRUITCAKE AGAIN?

26:31.857 --> 26:33.958
Ben:
UGH, PROBABLY.

26:33.960 --> 26:37.361
BUT YOU COULD OFFER TO MAKE
ANOTHER DESSERT AND SAVE US.

26:37.363 --> 26:39.363
CAN'T WE JUST SKIP
HIS CHRISTMAS PARTY?

26:39.365 --> 26:41.198
IT'S SO BORING.

26:41.200 --> 26:43.867
IT IS, BUT IT'S IMPORTANT
TO YOUR MOTHER --

26:43.869 --> 26:45.035
IT'S HER FAMILY.

26:45.037 --> 26:47.171
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

26:49.809 --> 26:50.641
[ BEEP ]

26:50.643 --> 26:51.675
HEY, WHAT'S UP?

26:51.677 --> 26:53.844
CHRISTY: Hi.
What did Cornell say?

26:53.846 --> 26:55.346
UH, NO BIG DEAL.

26:55.348 --> 26:56.880
I CAN TELL YOU
WHEN I COME GET YOU.

26:56.882 --> 26:58.282
Oh, well, actually,
you're off the hook.

26:58.284 --> 27:00.751
Turns out
I don't need a ride.

27:00.753 --> 27:01.819
IS EVERYTHING OKAY?

27:01.821 --> 27:03.621
Yeah, yeah,
everything's fine.

27:03.623 --> 27:04.955
I have a lift
to the body shop.

27:04.957 --> 27:06.156
MAN:
Christy, let's go.

27:06.158 --> 27:07.625
WHO'S THAT?

27:07.627 --> 27:09.760
I-I got to go.
Uh, I'll see you later.

27:09.762 --> 27:10.828
[ BEEP ]

27:14.967 --> 27:16.767
[ SIGHS ]

27:18.771 --> 27:20.971
ALL RIGHT,
I THINK YOU'RE GOOD.

27:20.973 --> 27:22.006
Dave: THANK YOU.

27:23.776 --> 27:24.809
HUH.

27:24.810 --> 27:25.843
DID YOU
FIND THE JACKET YET?

27:25.845 --> 27:27.911
DON'T YOU THINK
I WOULD'VE TOLD YOU?

27:27.913 --> 27:29.380
THAT'S A GOOD POINT.

27:29.382 --> 27:33.951
SO, THE WORKING THEORY
IS STILL TYLER?

27:33.953 --> 27:35.953
I'M NOT CRAZY.

27:35.954 --> 27:37.954
DOES ANYBODY THAT<i> IS</i> ACTUALLY
KNOW THAT THEY ARE, BEN?

27:38.958 --> 27:41.525
FINE.

27:41.526 --> 27:44.093
SO, IF I WAS A SHRINK,
I WOULD SAY, GO TO THE SOURCE.

27:44.096 --> 27:46.397
I WOULD SAY,
TALK TO MATT.

27:46.399 --> 27:48.432
[ SCOFFS ]
HE'S NONVERBAL.

27:48.434 --> 27:49.967
THAT IS NOT TRUE, MAN --

27:49.969 --> 27:52.403
THE WHOLE -- THAT COMPUTER-Y
THING THAT HE DOES.

27:52.405 --> 27:55.039
HE'S, LIKE,
A SUPER GENIUS, MAN.

27:55.041 --> 27:56.674
WE TALK.
WE HAVE LONG TALKS.

27:56.676 --> 27:58.976
HE GETS ME.

27:58.978 --> 28:00.177
WHAT COULD IT HURT?

28:03.249 --> 28:05.349
YOU KNOW VERY WELL
WHAT I'M TALKING ABOUT.
Natalie:
NO, I DON'T!

28:05.351 --> 28:06.984
VANESSA
TOLD ME EVERYTHING!

28:06.986 --> 28:08.419
I TRUSTED YOU
WITH MY SON,

28:08.421 --> 28:09.853
AND YOU PAWNED HIM OFF
LIKE A STRAY DOG?!

28:09.855 --> 28:11.989
OKAY, I LEFT TOM
WITH VANESSA ONCE!

28:11.991 --> 28:13.791
WHAT ABOUT THE G.I. JOE?
THAT WAS YOU, WASN'T IT?

28:13.793 --> 28:14.792
SO WHAT?

28:14.794 --> 28:16.193
TOM WANTED
TO SEE HIS FATHER!

28:16.195 --> 28:18.962
HE WAS<i> MY</i> SON,
AND I SAID NO.

28:18.964 --> 28:20.864
YOU NEED TO LEARN THE DIFFERENCE
BETWEEN RIGHT AND WRONG!

28:20.866 --> 28:22.032
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?!

28:22.034 --> 28:23.701
YOU SLEPT WITH MY DAD!

28:23.703 --> 28:25.002
YOU MADE A BABY
WITH HIM!
NATALIE --

28:25.004 --> 28:25.936
WHAT IS RIGHT
ABOUT THAT?!
NATALIE.

28:25.938 --> 28:26.837
NATALIE!

28:26.839 --> 28:28.038
GET IN THE HOUSE.

28:28.040 --> 28:30.741
[ BREATHES HEAVILY ]

28:30.743 --> 28:32.876
JESS,
WHAT'S GOING ON?

28:36.949 --> 28:38.082
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

28:38.084 --> 28:39.483
Reporter:
JESS, JUST ONE, PLEASE!

28:39.485 --> 28:41.151
[ DOOR SLAMS ]

28:43.089 --> 28:45.756
TELL ME AGAIN
HOW SORRY YOU ARE.

28:45.758 --> 28:47.875
GET IT OVER WITH
AND LEAVE ME ALONE.

28:47.876 --> 28:49.993
YOU KNOW WHAT? I'M TIRED
OF YOU TALKING TO ME LIKE THAT.

28:49.995 --> 28:51.862
I ALREADY APOLOGIZED.

28:51.864 --> 28:53.997
THIS ISN'T ABOUT ME.
LOOK...

28:53.999 --> 28:56.133
SHE'S THE ONE
WHO CAME OVER HERE.

28:56.135 --> 28:58.135
HER SON IS DEAD.

28:58.137 --> 29:01.071
SO WHAT?! SCREWING SOMEONE
ELSE'S HUSBAND DOESN'T MATTER?!

29:01.073 --> 29:03.273
EVERYONE MAKES MISTAKES.

29:03.275 --> 29:05.275
JESS ISN'T EVIL.
SHE'S HUMAN.

29:05.277 --> 29:06.343
BUT WHAT YOU GUYS DID...

29:06.345 --> 29:07.811
IT HAPPENED!

29:07.813 --> 29:09.913
AND I CAN'T CHANGE IT,

29:09.914 --> 29:12.014
BUT I TOOK RESPONSIBILITY FOR IT
BECAUSE THAT'S WHAT YOU DO --

29:12.017 --> 29:13.350
YOU OWN YOUR MISTAKES.

29:25.765 --> 29:27.882
LEAVE US ALONE.

29:27.883 --> 29:30.000
COME ON, LISA, I JUST NEED
TO TALK TO MATT FOR ONE MINUTE.

29:30.002 --> 29:32.102
I KNOW WHAT YOU DID
TO JOE AND VANESSA.

29:32.104 --> 29:33.170
WHAT IS WRONG WITH YOU?

29:33.172 --> 29:35.339
I WILL NOT
LET YOU NEAR MY SON.

29:35.341 --> 29:37.407
I SAVED MATT'S LIFE!

29:37.409 --> 29:39.276
I WOULD NEVER HURT HIM, LISA.
YOU KNOW THAT!

29:39.278 --> 29:40.344
[ GLASS SHATTERS ]

29:40.346 --> 29:41.211
WHAT WAS THAT?

29:41.213 --> 29:42.012
WAS THAT TYLER?

29:42.014 --> 29:43.514
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

29:43.516 --> 29:44.548
NO!

29:44.550 --> 29:45.382
TYLER!

29:45.384 --> 29:46.950
BEN, STOP!

29:46.952 --> 29:48.552
I WANT YOU OUT OF HERE.
I'M CALLING KEVIN.

29:53.292 --> 29:55.826
LISA, WHAT THE HELL'S
GOING ON IN HERE?

30:04.470 --> 30:06.687
TYLER?
YOU UP HERE?
BEN, WHAT
ARE YOU DOING?!

30:06.688 --> 30:08.905
Lisa:
GET OUT OF MY HOUSE!
I KNOW YOU'RE HIDING HIM,
AND I KNOW HE'S HERE!

30:08.908 --> 30:10.340
YOU SEE?
I TOLD TYLER IS NOT HERE.

30:10.342 --> 30:12.126
WHERE'S MATT?
NOW YOU HAVE TO LEAVE.

30:12.127 --> 30:13.911
IS THIS HIS ROOM?
MATT?!
NO, BEN, DON'T GO
IN MATT'S ROOM!

30:13.913 --> 30:16.046
MATTY. MATT! MATT.
IT'S OKAY, IT'S OKAY.

30:16.048 --> 30:18.048
I KNOW. I-I'M JUST
MAKING SURE YOU'RE OKAY!
IT'S OKAY.

30:18.050 --> 30:20.350
<i> MATT'S ROOM -- PRIVATE.</i>

30:20.352 --> 30:22.219
MATTY, MATTY,
WHERE IS TYLER?!

30:22.221 --> 30:23.453
BEN, PLEASE LEAVE!

30:23.455 --> 30:25.189
ALL RIGHT, ALL RIGHT.
Matty: [ WHIMPERING ]

30:25.191 --> 30:26.390
ALL RIGHT,
MAMA'S GOT YOU.

30:26.392 --> 30:28.559
UH -- I KNOW.

30:28.561 --> 30:29.927
I-I KNOW.

30:29.929 --> 30:31.929
SHH, SHH, SHH, SHH!

30:31.931 --> 30:32.596
IT'S OKAY.

30:32.598 --> 30:33.497
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

30:33.498 --> 30:34.397
I-I KNOW.
IT'S OKAY.

30:34.400 --> 30:36.099
DOES TYLER
HIDE THINGS IN HERE?!

30:36.101 --> 30:37.868
[ MOANING ]
IT'S ALL RIGHT.
<i> BEN OUT.</i>

30:37.870 --> 30:39.937
BEN, PLEASE LEAVE.
IS TYLER HERE?!

30:39.939 --> 30:41.038
[ MOANS ]
OKAY, OKAY.

30:41.040 --> 30:42.940
[ MOANING ]
OKAY. GOT YOU.

30:42.942 --> 30:44.508
<i> MATT'S THINGS.</i>

30:44.510 --> 30:45.909
NO, BEN, PLEASE DON'T
TOUCH MATT'S THINGS!

30:45.911 --> 30:47.945
DON'T T-- MATTY.
MATT!

30:47.947 --> 30:48.545
[ SHOUTING ]
MATT!

30:48.547 --> 30:49.913
HEY!

30:49.914 --> 30:51.280
HEY!
I'M NOT GONNA TAKE ANYTHING!

30:51.283 --> 30:53.050
WHERE IS YOUR BROTHER?

30:53.052 --> 30:54.351
[ GRUNTS ]
WHERE IS
YOUR BROTHER, MATTY?!

30:54.353 --> 30:55.519
WHERE
IS YOUR BROTHER?!

30:55.521 --> 30:57.421
[ GRUNTING ]
NO, NO, MATT.
MATT, STOP.

30:57.423 --> 30:59.590
MATT?
MATT, MATT, 4:00!

30:59.592 --> 31:01.358
HEY! HEY, MATT!
4:00, BUD!

31:01.360 --> 31:04.094
HEY, IT'S 4:00.
WHAT DO WE DO AT 4:00?

31:04.096 --> 31:05.996
WE GO TO THE CHAIR.
YES.

31:05.998 --> 31:08.031
AT 4:00, WE GET
A CHAIR HUG, MATT. COME ON.
[ PANTING ]

31:08.033 --> 31:09.900
CALM.
COME ON, BUD.
READY?

31:09.902 --> 31:11.001
COME ON.
HERE WE GO.
[ PANTING ]

31:11.003 --> 31:12.035
THERE YOU GO.

31:12.037 --> 31:13.403
YOU'RE OKAY, MATTY.

31:13.405 --> 31:14.605
YOU'RE OKAY.

31:14.607 --> 31:16.473
YOU'RE OKAY.

31:16.475 --> 31:17.975
GET OUT.

31:17.977 --> 31:19.143
GET OUT!

31:19.144 --> 31:20.310
THE WALLS AND YOUR --
YOUR LIP.

31:20.312 --> 31:21.411
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

31:21.413 --> 31:23.080
TYLER DIDN'T KILL TOM.

31:23.082 --> 31:25.649
YOU THINK THAT MATT DID IT?
YOU'RE INSANE.

31:25.651 --> 31:27.017
I'M CALLING THE POLICE.

31:27.019 --> 31:29.253
WAIT!

31:29.255 --> 31:32.022
WAIT.

31:32.024 --> 31:35.225
YOU HAVE NO IDEA
HOW HARD IT'S BEEN SINCE TOM...

31:37.062 --> 31:39.029
I'M NOT TALKING ABOUT
YOUR LOSS.

31:39.031 --> 31:41.298
THAT'S UNIMAGINABLE.

31:41.300 --> 31:43.467
BUT YOU KNOW MATTY.

31:43.469 --> 31:45.669
YOU KNOW THAT HE NEEDS
STRUCTURE AND ROUTINE

31:45.671 --> 31:48.322
AND A SENSE OF ORDER,

31:48.323 --> 31:50.974
AND WITH THE POLICE AND THE
REPORTERS AND ALL OF THE NOISE,

31:50.976 --> 31:52.209
HE GETS UPSET.

31:52.211 --> 31:53.977
UPSET?

31:53.979 --> 31:56.046
LISA, LOOK AT
YOUR HOUSE, YOUR --

31:56.048 --> 31:57.180
THAT'S --
I KNOW, I KNOW.

31:57.182 --> 31:59.049
I KNOW HOW IT LOOKS,

31:59.050 --> 32:00.917
BUT THE ONLY ONE THAT MATT
IS A DANGER TO IS HIMSELF.

32:00.920 --> 32:03.253
NO, HE MAY NOT MEAN IT,
BUT MATT IS VIOLENT.

32:03.255 --> 32:05.956
WELL, H-HE LASHES OUT,
BUT I TOLD YOU,

32:05.958 --> 32:07.925
IT'S BECAUSE OF EVERYTHING
THAT'S BEEN GOING ON.

32:07.927 --> 32:09.259
ONCE IT STOPS,
HE'LL BE FINE.

32:09.261 --> 32:10.961
IF HE CAN DO THIS TO YOU,
HIS MOTHER,

32:10.963 --> 32:12.562
WHO ELSE COULD HE HURT?

32:12.564 --> 32:14.498
DID HE HURT TOM?

32:14.499 --> 32:16.433
OH, YOU KNOW THAT MATT
WAS NEVER ALONE WITH TOM.

32:16.435 --> 32:18.936
BUT HOW WOULD YOU KNOW?
YOU DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
HE WAS IN THE RIVER.

32:18.938 --> 32:20.370
WHO THE HELL
DO YOU THINK YOU ARE?

32:20.372 --> 32:22.439
MY MOM IS DOING
THE BEST SHE CAN.

32:22.441 --> 32:24.341
IF SHE SAYS THAT MATT WASN'T
WITH TOM, THEN HE WASN'T.

32:24.343 --> 32:25.943
LIKE SHE SAID
THAT YOU WEREN'T HOME?

32:25.945 --> 32:28.045
YEAH, THAT'S ABOUT ME,
NOT TOM.

32:28.047 --> 32:29.446
TYLER, DON'T.
NO, ENOUGH!

32:29.448 --> 32:30.948
AND I KNOW
ABOUT THE REHAB.

32:30.950 --> 32:32.750
OH, GOOD FOR YOU!

32:32.751 --> 32:34.551
THEN YOU KNOW THAT I'VE PUT
MY MOM THROUGH HELL THREE TIMES,

32:34.553 --> 32:36.286
AND EVEN NOW,
AFTER EVERYTHING THAT HAPPENED,

32:36.288 --> 32:37.921
SHE STILL
LETS ME STAY HERE.

32:37.922 --> 32:39.555
WHAT HAPPENED?
WHAT -- WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

32:39.558 --> 32:41.191
HE'S NOT
SAYING ANYTHING.

32:41.193 --> 32:42.960
I ASKED HIM TO COME HOME
AND TO HELP ME WITH MATT.

32:42.962 --> 32:44.394
HE CAME TO HELP ME
WITH MATTY.

32:44.396 --> 32:45.429
THEN WHY HIDE?

32:45.431 --> 32:46.430
HE'S NOT HIDING.

32:46.432 --> 32:47.915
MOM!

32:47.916 --> 32:49.399
WHEN YOU DRIVE WASTED,
YOU HURT PEOPLE!

32:49.401 --> 32:51.368
WE DON'T KNOW
THAT THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.

32:51.370 --> 32:53.737
I LEFT THE SCENE,
AND I DITCHED THE CAR.

32:53.739 --> 32:55.706
THAT IS EXACTLY
WHAT HAPPENED!

32:57.009 --> 32:58.075
[ SIGHS ]

32:59.345 --> 33:02.179
MY MOM IS LETTING ME
HIDE HERE AND, UH...

33:02.181 --> 33:03.981
[ SIGHS ]
LISTEN...

33:03.983 --> 33:06.516
I MESSED UP, BUT...

33:06.518 --> 33:09.119
I'M CLEAN NOW,
AND I'VE BEEN CLEAN.

33:09.121 --> 33:10.554
OKAY [SPUTTERS]

33:10.556 --> 33:13.290
HOW DID MATT
GET THE BLUE JACKET?

33:13.291 --> 33:16.025
BEN, YOU CAN LOOK ALL OVER
THIS HOUSE FOR THAT JACKET,

33:16.028 --> 33:17.594
BUT I'M TRYING
TO PROTECT MY SON --

33:17.596 --> 33:19.229
PLEASE DON'T
CALL THE POLICE.

33:19.231 --> 33:22.032
OH, COME ON, YOU DO NOT
HAVE TO PROTECT ME ANYMORE.

33:22.034 --> 33:24.034
YOU SHOULDN'T.
IT DOESN'T HELP.

33:24.036 --> 33:26.503
BESIDES,
I-I TOOK CARE OF IT, SO...

33:26.505 --> 33:29.106
WAIT, W-W-WHAT DO YOU MEAN?!
WHAT DID YOU DO?!

33:30.709 --> 33:32.209
CALLED THE COPS.

33:32.211 --> 33:35.145
THEY'RE ON THEIR WAY.

33:36.148 --> 33:38.448
Ben: I DON'T KNOW HOW THE HELL
HE GOT MY FLASHLIGHT.

33:38.450 --> 33:40.083
ALL I KNOW IS,
HE'S VIOLENT.

33:40.085 --> 33:41.718
YOU'RE TRYING
TO DO MY JOB, MR. CRAWFORD,

33:41.720 --> 33:43.554
AND YOU'RE TERRIBLE
AT IT.

33:43.555 --> 33:45.389
MATT HAD THE BLUE JACKET
WITH THE BLOODSTAIN!

33:45.391 --> 33:47.091
YOU ACTUALLY THINK

33:47.092 --> 33:48.792
THAT AN AUTISTIC BOY
BROKE INTO YOUR TRUCK,

33:48.794 --> 33:51.194
STOLE YOUR FLASHLIGHT,
LURED TOM OUT INTO THE WOOD,

33:51.196 --> 33:52.262
AND KILLED HIM?

33:52.264 --> 33:53.530
I'M NOT SAYING
HE PLANNED IT.

33:53.532 --> 33:55.165
I'M SAYING MAYBE
THERE WAS AN ACCIDENT,

33:55.167 --> 33:56.700
AND THEN TYLER TOOK
THE JACKET FROM THE WOODS

33:56.702 --> 33:58.702
TO COVER FOR HIS BROTHER

33:58.703 --> 34:00.703
'CAUSE THAT'S WHAT THIS FAMILY
DOES -- THEY COVER.

34:02.674 --> 34:04.541
I THINK
YOU'RE LOSING YOUR MIND.

34:05.377 --> 34:07.277
IT WAS RAINING
THE NIGHT TOM WAS KILLED.

34:07.279 --> 34:08.111
SO?

34:08.113 --> 34:09.546
ACCORDING TO LISA DALY,

34:09.548 --> 34:11.415
YOU KNOW THAT MATT
IS TERRIFIED OF THE RAIN.

34:11.417 --> 34:13.784
HE HATES THE WAY IT FEELS
PELTING HIS SKIN.

34:13.786 --> 34:15.419
IF IT'S RAINING,
HE WON'T GO OUTSIDE.

34:15.421 --> 34:16.586
THAT'S YOUR PROOF?

34:16.588 --> 34:18.538
RAIN?

34:18.539 --> 34:20.489
AND MATT'S GPS BRACELET
HAS HIM AT HOME IN BED

34:20.492 --> 34:21.758
WHEN TOM WAS KILLED.

34:21.760 --> 34:23.160
THAT GOOD ENOUGH
FOR YOU?

34:23.162 --> 34:24.979
[ SIGHS ]

34:24.980 --> 34:26.797
YOU NEED TO STOP SCORCHING
THE EARTH, MR. CRAWFORD.

34:26.799 --> 34:30.400
YOU'RE HURTING YOUR FAMILY,
YOUR FRIENDS, YOUR NEIGHBORHOOD.

34:30.402 --> 34:33.703
IF YOU KEEP PUSHING,
SOMEONE'S GONNA PUSH BACK.

34:40.479 --> 34:42.679
[ DOOR OPENS ]

34:44.149 --> 34:46.683
Natalie: THIS HAS GOT TO BE
ONE OF YOURS, RIGHT, DAD?

34:46.685 --> 34:48.986
YOUR CHOICE --

34:48.987 --> 34:51.288
STOP SHAKING GIFTS NOW OR GET
NOTHING CHRISTMAS MORNING.

34:51.290 --> 34:52.823
I THINK
I SHOULD REWRAP IT.

34:52.825 --> 34:55.225
YEAH, DAD,
IT'S A MESS.

34:55.227 --> 34:56.493
[ CHUCKLES ]
LET ME SEE THAT.

34:56.495 --> 34:58.161
IT'S NOT THAT BAD.
IT'S...
IT'S PRETTY BAD.

34:58.163 --> 35:00.630
[ KNOCK ON DOOR ]
[ CHUCKLES ]

35:06.672 --> 35:09.306
[ LOCK DISENGAGES ]

35:09.308 --> 35:11.241
I FOUND YOUR VANDAL.

35:11.243 --> 35:14.678
Natalie:
WHAT THE HELL?

35:14.680 --> 35:16.580
SPEAK, MR. COOPER.

35:18.851 --> 35:21.585
Cooper:
[ SIGHS ]

35:21.586 --> 35:24.320
I TAGGED YOUR FENCE AND MESSED
UP MRS. CRAWFORD'S CAR.

35:24.323 --> 35:25.489
WHY?

35:25.491 --> 35:27.858
BECAUSE...

35:27.860 --> 35:30.127
HE WOULDN'T
LET ME SEE YOU.

35:30.129 --> 35:32.762
I TRIED TO CALL
WHEN WE WERE ALL AT NOAH'S.

35:32.764 --> 35:35.899
TOM HAD JUST DIED.

35:35.901 --> 35:37.501
THERE WERE OTHER TIMES.

35:37.503 --> 35:40.137
THE CAR WAS FOR THE THING
AT MY PARTY.

35:41.206 --> 35:43.907
I WAS HIGH. IT WAS STUPID.
I'M SORRY.

35:43.909 --> 35:45.175
REALLY.

35:45.177 --> 35:46.643
I AM SORRY.

35:47.613 --> 35:48.979
DO YOU WANT
TO PRESS CHARGES?

35:52.784 --> 35:53.884
NO.

35:53.886 --> 35:55.485
BUT I AM
CALLING YOUR PARENTS,

35:55.487 --> 35:56.753
AND YOU'RE GONNA PAY
FOR THE DAMAGE.

35:56.755 --> 35:59.556
AND YOU CAN ALSO
GET THE HELL AWAY FROM MY HOUSE.

35:59.558 --> 36:00.924
WE'RE DONE.
NAT, COME ON.

36:00.926 --> 36:02.792
Abby:
YOU HEARD HER!

36:02.794 --> 36:04.895
YOU'RE DONE-ZO!

36:04.897 --> 36:06.696
YOU'RE FREE TO LEAVE.

36:08.167 --> 36:09.699
THANK YOU, MA'AM.

36:12.871 --> 36:14.771
WELL, I'M GLAD
THAT'S OVER.

36:14.773 --> 36:16.907
Cornell:
IT'S NOT OVER, MR. CRAWFORD.

36:16.909 --> 36:20.277
A THREAT ASSESSMENT
CONFIRMED MY INITIAL THEORY

36:20.279 --> 36:22.062
THAT THE FLASHLIGHTS

36:22.063 --> 36:23.846
ARE COMPLETELY UNRELATED
TO MR. COOPER'S VANDALISM.

36:27.386 --> 36:28.552
ARE YOU SURE?

36:28.554 --> 36:30.687
THE PERSON WHO
BROKE INTO YOUR GARAGE

36:30.689 --> 36:32.856
IS EXTREMELY SKILLED
AND DANGEROUS.

36:32.858 --> 36:35.358
MY KIDS COULD
BREAK INTO MY GARAGE.

36:35.360 --> 36:37.894
PERHAPS, BUT I HIGHLY DOUBT
THEY COULD SEND ME

36:37.896 --> 36:40.197
A TEXT MESSAGE
FROM YOUR TELEPHONE NUMBER

36:40.199 --> 36:41.665
THAT'S UNTRACEABLE.

36:43.635 --> 36:45.335
YOU CAN'T FIGURE OUT
WHERE IT CAME FROM?

36:45.337 --> 36:49.439
I NEED YOU TO MAKE A LIST
OF ANYONE YOU'VE ANGERED LATELY,

36:49.441 --> 36:52.842
AND IF THIS ESCALATES
IN ANY WAY, PLEASE...

36:52.844 --> 36:53.910
CONTACT ME.

36:53.912 --> 36:56.246
[ SIGHS ]
I DON'T GET IT.

36:56.248 --> 36:57.614
WHY DO YOU CARE?

36:58.884 --> 37:02.352
TO PROTECT AND SERVE,
MR. CRAWFORD -

37:02.354 --> 37:03.987
THAT'S THE JOB.

37:09.761 --> 37:13.230
[ INDISTINCT TALKING ]

37:13.232 --> 37:15.632
Tyler: YEAH,
REHAB WAS INTERESTING.

37:15.634 --> 37:17.567
IT'S DEFINITELY NOT SOMETHING
I WANT TO DO OVER AGAIN.

37:17.569 --> 37:18.802
[ TALKING CONTINUES ]

37:18.804 --> 37:20.437
BUT IT WAS HELPFUL?
YEAH.

37:20.439 --> 37:22.772
MR. CRAWFORD.

37:22.774 --> 37:25.609
TYLER, I'M REALLY SORRY
ABOUT THE OTHER --

37:25.611 --> 37:26.943
HEY.
NO WORRIES, MAN.

37:26.945 --> 37:28.411
SINCE I TURNED MYSELF IN,

37:28.413 --> 37:30.513
THE DETECTIVE
REALLY WENT TO BAT FOR ME.

37:30.515 --> 37:33.783
WELL, ALSO, 'CAUSE, YOU KNOW,
YOU DIDN'T KILL ANYONE.

37:33.785 --> 37:35.952
[ CHUCKLES ]
YEAH, YEAH, THERE'S THAT.

37:35.954 --> 37:38.755
[ CHUCKLES ] JUST, UH,
DEMOLISHED A ROW OF MAILBOXES.

37:38.757 --> 37:41.491
[ BOTH CHUCKLE ]

37:41.493 --> 37:43.760
BUT, UH, YEAH,
SHE'S RECOMMENDING HOUSE ARREST

37:43.762 --> 37:46.263
AND COMMUNITY SERVICE,
SO, YEAH, I GUESS I'M LUCKY.

37:46.265 --> 37:47.831
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

37:47.833 --> 37:50.267
THAT'S GOOD NEWS.
BET MOM'S RELIEVED.

37:50.269 --> 37:52.669
HOW IS SHE?

37:52.671 --> 37:53.959
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

37:53.960 --> 37:55.248
EH, SHE'S DOING
ALL RIGHT.

37:55.249 --> 37:56.537
I DON'T KNOW
IF IT'S A GOOD IDEA

37:56.541 --> 37:59.609
FOR YOU TO COME OVER
ANYTIME SOON. [ CHUCKLES ]

37:59.611 --> 38:01.444
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
ANYWAYS...

38:01.446 --> 38:03.313
SEE YOU LATER, NAT.

38:03.315 --> 38:04.648
SEE YA.

38:04.650 --> 38:05.749
[ SNIFFS ]

38:09.855 --> 38:10.987
WHERE ARE YOU GOING?

38:13.625 --> 38:15.025
YOU TOLD ME TO OWN IT.

38:16.028 --> 38:17.427
NAT,
THAT'S REALLY...

38:17.429 --> 38:20.330
I KNOW, I KNOW.
YOU'RE PROUD OF ME.

38:20.332 --> 38:22.032
Man:
NATALIE, ONE QUESTION, PLEASE!

38:22.034 --> 38:23.800
[ INDISTINCT SHOUTING ]

38:23.802 --> 38:25.268
PLEASE, NATALIE!

38:25.269 --> 38:26.735
Man #2: WHAT'S YOUR RELATIONSHIP
WITH TYLER?

38:30.609 --> 38:32.042
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKS ]

38:32.044 --> 38:33.677
HEY.

38:33.679 --> 38:35.478
I JUST WANTED TO APOLOGIZE
FOR WHAT I SAID.

38:38.850 --> 38:39.949
THANKS.

38:39.951 --> 38:41.985
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

38:57.569 --> 39:00.670
Woman: YES?
Man:
COULD YOU GET THIS STARTED?

39:03.775 --> 39:05.675
WHAT ARE YOU
DOING HERE?

39:05.677 --> 39:08.478
I JUST CAME TO GIVE YOU
AN UPDATE.

39:08.480 --> 39:09.679
NAT CALLED ALREADY.

39:09.681 --> 39:12.015
I GUESS, YOU KNOW,
WE DON'T HAVE TO WORRY

39:12.017 --> 39:14.417
ABOUT COOPER
COMING AROUND ANYMORE.

39:14.419 --> 39:16.820
FOR NOW.
MM.

39:16.822 --> 39:20.824
WELL, I WAS JUST GONNA LEAVE
TO MEET A CLIENT, SO...

39:22.527 --> 39:23.593
AT NIGHT?

39:23.595 --> 39:25.929
[ INDISTINCT TALKING
IN DISTANCE ]

39:27.632 --> 39:28.865
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

39:36.074 --> 39:38.975
THIS REALLY
ISN'T THE TIME.

39:38.977 --> 39:40.944
DO YOU EVEN KNOW?

39:40.946 --> 39:43.980
HOW CAN I POSSIBLY
ANSWER THAT RIGHT NOW?

39:47.719 --> 39:49.886
YOU CAN TRY.

39:51.757 --> 39:53.890
A 5-YEAR-OLD
IS DEAD.

39:53.892 --> 39:56.826
YOU SLEPT WITH THE WOMAN
ACROSS THE STREET,

39:56.828 --> 39:58.862
AND EVERY TIME
I SEE HER...

39:58.864 --> 40:02.599
A SLIDE SHOW OF THE TWO OF YOU
JUST RUNS THROUGH MY HEAD,

40:02.601 --> 40:04.667
AND I WANT TO KILL YOU.

40:06.638 --> 40:08.104
BUT A 5-YEAR-OLD
IS DEAD.

40:10.075 --> 40:14.644
I CAN'T SCREAM,
I CAN'T YELL, I CAN'T CRY.

40:14.646 --> 40:18.448
I CAN'T MOURN THE LOSS
OF MY DIGNITY, I CAN'T...

40:18.450 --> 40:19.883
I CAN'T FEEL
WHAT I'M FEELING...

40:22.087 --> 40:24.988
...BECAUSE
A 5-YEAR-OLD IS DEAD.

40:27.025 --> 40:28.925
I HATE YOU.

40:28.927 --> 40:31.594
AND I LOVE YOU.

40:31.596 --> 40:34.964
AND YOU'RE A SUSPECT
IN A MURDER.

40:36.735 --> 40:38.134
AND I WANT TO STAY.

40:38.136 --> 40:40.870
AND I WANT TO RUN
FOR THE HILLS.

40:40.872 --> 40:42.205
SO...

40:43.875 --> 40:46.042
I CAN'T TELL YOU
WHAT I WANT...

40:48.480 --> 40:50.947
...BECAUSE
A 5-YEAR-OLD IS DEAD.

40:50.949 --> 40:53.650
AND HE WAS YOUR SON.

41:02.928 --> 41:03.893
[ KEYS JINGLING ]

41:03.895 --> 41:05.462
[ CAR ALARM BEEPS ]

41:14.873 --> 41:16.840
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

41:16.841 --> 41:18.808
¶ SUCH A LIE WHEN YOU WEAR
RIGHTEOUS GRIN ¶

41:18.810 --> 41:21.177
¶ 'CAUSE THE SUN,
IT BURNS YOUR SKIN ¶

41:21.179 --> 41:23.480
¶ HELL, I NEVER WIN,
AND I SAID, "OH" ¶

41:23.482 --> 41:25.048
[ CELLPHONE BEEPS ]

41:25.050 --> 41:26.483
¶ WELL, I'M NEVER COMING BACK ¶

41:26.485 --> 41:28.518
¶ I'VE DONE ALL THAT I CAN DO ¶

41:28.520 --> 41:32.188
¶ YEAH, I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF THAT,
AND I SAID, "OH" ¶

41:32.190 --> 41:35.892
¶ WELL, I'M NEVER COMING BACK,
AND I'VE HAD ENOUGH OF YOU ¶

41:35.894 --> 41:37.961
¶ JUST ADMIT
THAT THIS IS THROUGH ¶

41:37.963 --> 41:40.897
[ MUSIC STOPS ]

41:54.112 --> 41:55.778
[ LOCKS ENGAGE ]

41:56.948 --> 41:57.914
[ DOOR HANDLE RATTLING ]

41:57.916 --> 41:58.982
[ GRUNTS ]

42:01.152 --> 42:03.019
[ DOOR HANDLE RATTLING ]

42:06.625 --> 42:08.091
HEY!
[ POUNDING ]

42:08.093 --> 42:09.125
HEY!
